; Issue: https://github.com/rustledger/rustledger/issues/333
; Description: Interpolation error with stock purchase when cost has more decimal
;              places than other postings in the transaction.
; Expected: No errors - interpolated amount should preserve cost spec precision
;
; The bug was that the interpolated Cash posting was rounded to 0 decimal places
; (from the "1 CAD" commission) instead of 2 decimal places (from the cost spec
; "2800.01 CAD"), resulting in -2801.00 CAD instead of -2801.01 CAD.

2026-01-01 commodity CAD
2026-01-01 commodity CSU

2026-01-01 open Assets:Cash-CAD CAD
2026-01-01 open Assets:Stock-CAD:CSU CSU
2026-01-01 open Equity:Equity-CAD CAD
2026-01-01 open Expenses:Commission-CAD CAD

2026-01-02 * "Opening balance"
  Assets:Cash-CAD                          2801.02 CAD
  Equity:Equity-CAD

2026-01-19 * "Buy stock"
  Assets:Stock-CAD:CSU   1 CSU { 2800.01 CAD }
  Expenses:Commission-CAD              1 CAD
  Assets:Cash-CAD
